column8: Pareto Care is technology enabled healthcare services company focused towards reducing Congestive Heart Failure (CHF) hospitalisations and readmissions. We are building a wearable biosensor platform to monitor patient hemodynamic parameters important in managing CHF treatment. Our solution includes a three stage process; monitoring, predicting and intervening. We monitor clinical parameters that detect early deterioration; using this data we predict CHF exacerbations and then work with clinicians to manage treatment in order to avoid hospitalisation. Our wearable biosensor platform includes two wearable medical devices; a wrist watch and a chest patch. Together these devices continuously, non-invasively and remotely monitor 8 parameters including Arterial Blood Pressure, Cardiac Output, Stroke Volume, and Thoracic Fluid Content. Our clinician interfacing web application allows clinician's to continuously and remotely monitor patient hemodynamics, recieve customized alerts and exacerbation predictions, and recommendations for appropriate evidence-based interventions. Come join us in our journey to evolving our care systems from reactive to predictive!

column8: Between 2015 and 2030, the number of people in the world aged 60 years or over is expected to grow by 56%, from just over 900 million to nearly 1.5 billion. This trend in turn leads to an increase in the number of people requiring long-term skilled care (LTSC), which includes home care, hospices, nursing homes, and assisted living centers. One of the most common issues in LTSC settings is falls. One in every 3 people older than 65 years is estimated to fall 1 or more times each year. Fall death rates among adults age 65 and older increased more than 30% from 2007 to 2016. Every 19 minutes, an older adult dies from a fall. Falls in older adults are not only risky, but also costly. In 2019, falls of US residents aged 65 or older led to $51B in medical costs, with $39B paid for by Medicare/Medicaid and $12B paid by private entities. Falls are also the 2nd largest reason for lawsuits against LTSCs. Heron Point Tech’s Fall Prevention System allows assisted living facilities to preemptively and continuously detect residents who are likely to fall. As opposed to most fall-related systems, our system doesn’t detect falls - it stops them from happening in the first place. By using our camera-based system to track resident walking patterns/gaits, residents are assigned weekly fall risk scores. No wearable devices required.

column8: Blockchains are the most open, public and up-to-data data sources we have ever experienced. Data on blockchain though is extremely noisy, hard to read and even harder to make sense of them. Openstory was created in order to organize and democratize the access of blockchain data so users can make educated decisions, based on information and knowledge that before was only available to highly technical funds and companies. What’s happening on-chain Openstory is not a siloed API aggregator, a hand-picked catalog, or a centralized recommendation web2 service. Openstory is an indexer that focuses on scanning and unveiling on-chain truth like a story so everyone can easily make decisions based on objective information. What you see in the platform is not a recommendation from an employee or the curated information of APIs; instead, our database starts and ends with indexing the public on-chain information, offering a pure outcome of how people use and interact with web3. How challenging is this? Mapping web3 is both a data intelligence challenge and a UX challenge. How do we display the information meaningfully and drive usage beyond? How deep do we go? Your feedback is essential to its success, so we'd love you to be part of this journey early on. How to use Openstory The initial token/NFT sale can be the beginning of the experience, not the end. A creator or a brand can use Openstory to see how web3 users use/interact with their creations, spot their audience (who is buying and what’s their engagement) and reward them accordingly. A collector can use Openstory to assess if an NFT is worth buying based on usage/investors attracted, discover the up-and-coming collections, meet other collectors/soulmates, and create deeper relationships with the artists they love. A flipper can discover the most recent collections that grow exponentially. Everyone can check key market metrics, e.g., active users in the market, market growth, and marketplaces with the highest traction, so they have a better picture of the market they invest their money and time.

column8: Total Wellness Innovations Inc. (TWI) leads the forefront of healthcare technology with our comprehensive Whole You mobile and web app, designed to revolutionize patient engagement and healthcare management. Whole You seamlessly integrates advanced technological solutions, including our proprietary APIs, to provide a customized, user-friendly, and efficient health management experience. Whole You is the embodiment of our vision, combining Electronic Health Records (EHRs) workflows with an intuitive user interface. It leverages the power of our APIs to deliver a holistic health management platform. This integration facilitates a more connected and personalized healthcare experience, making it easier for patients to manage their health and for healthcare providers to deliver optimal care. Our Medical Content Library API forms a crucial part of Whole You, serving as a centralized repository of evidence-based, medically reviewed content. It empowers patients with reliable and accessible medical information, enhancing their understanding and engagement with their health. In Whole You, this API provides users with a wealth of information at their fingertips, aiding in informed decision-making and patient education. The Patient Tracker API is another integral component of Whole You. It provides real-time tracking for key aspects of a patient's medical workflow, such as hydration, medication, nutrition, and exercise. This API ensures that all pertinent health data is up-to-date and easily accessible within the Whole You platform, enabling continuous monitoring and more effective health management. Lastly, our Clinical Translator API is pivotal in transforming unstructured and structured medical data into actionable insights. Within Whole You, it takes raw clinical information from EHRs and other medical documents and turns it into comprehensible Activities & Goals tailored to each patient's unique needs. This functionality is crucial for personalizing the healthcare experience and making complex medical data understandable and actionable for both patients and healthcare providers. At Total Wellness Innovations Inc., Whole You stands as a testament to our dedication to enhancing healthcare management through technology. By integrating our advanced APIs into this comprehensive platform, we are making strides in empowering patients, simplifying healthcare workflows, and paving the way for a more informed and engaged approach to health and wellness.
